{"lemma":"بِرازٌ","slug":"بِرازٌ","root":"ب.ر.ز","root_slug":"ب-ر-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2258","n2259"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feces, excrement, dung, stool; manure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"contest, competition, match; duel"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From بَرَزَ (baraza, “to come out, to emerge”) and بَارَزَ (bāraza, “to vie with to surpass”) from the root ب ر ز (b r z)."},"ipa":["/bi.raːz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2258","headword_ar":"بَرَازٌ","root":"brz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A field, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide expanse of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biraAzN","text_ar":"بِرَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this latter form is rare: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an open tract of land destitute of herbage and trees and without hills or mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which is no covert of trees or other things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an open place in which is no covert of trees or other things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an open place in which is no covert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraja A_ilaY AlbaraAzi","text_ar":"خَرَجَ اـِلَى البَرَازِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth to satisfy a want of nature."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA A^araAda AlbaraAza A^aboEada","text_ar":"اـِذَا اَرَادَ البَرَازَ اَبْعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When he desired to satisfy a want of nature, he went far off"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a trad.; respecting which El-Khattábee says that the relaters of traditions err respecting the word, pronouncing it with kesr, for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biraAzN","text_ar":"بِرَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.: but (SM says that) authorities differ as to this point. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [It is further said,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAzN","text_ar":"بَرَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biraAzN","text_ar":"بِرَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) is metonymically applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excrement; human ordure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feces of food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Mgh","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n2259","headword_ar":"بِرَازٌ","root":"brz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAzN","text_ar":"بَرَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}